  "prompt": "What hand drawn anime is out there?",
  "response": "There are numerous hand-drawn anime series and films that have been produced over the years, showcasing a wide range of styles, genres, and storytelling techniques. Here are some notable examples:\n\n### Classic Series:\n1. **Naruto** - A story about a young ninja seeking recognition and dreaming of becoming the Hokage.\n2. **Dragon Ball** - Follows the adventures of Goku from childhood to adulthood as he trains in martial arts and explores the world.\n3. **Sailor Moon** - Focuses on the adventures of a teenage girl named Usagi Tsukino who transforms into Sailor Moon to search for the \"Legendary Silver Crystal.\"\n4. **Neon Genesis Evangelion** - A complex and philosophical series about teenagers piloting giant mechs to protect Earth from mysterious beings called Angels.\n5. **Cowboy Bebop** - A space western featuring a group of bounty hunters traveling in their spaceship, the Bebop.\n\n### Modern Series:\n1. **Attack on Titan** - Centers on humanity's struggle against gigantic humanoid Titans.\n2. **My Hero Academia** - Follows a society where nearly everyone has superpowers, or \"Quirks,\" and focuses on a young boy without powers who dreams of becoming a hero.\n3. **Demon Slayer** - Chronicles the journey of Tanjiro Kamado, who becomes a demon slayer after his family is slaughtered and his sister is turned into a demon.\n4. **One Punch Man** - A superhero parody that follows Saitama, who can defeat any opponent with a single punch.\n5. **Jujutsu Kaisen** - Follows a high school student who joins a secret organization to fight cursed spirits and save his friends.\n\n### Films:\n1. **Spirited Away** - Directed by Hayao Miyazaki, this film follows a young girl who wanders into a world of spirits and gods.\n2. **My Neighbor Totoro** - Another Miyazaki classic about two young sisters who encounter friendly forest spirits in rural Japan.\n3. **Akira** - A groundbreaking cyberpunk film set in post-apocalyptic Tokyo.\n4. **Your Name** - A romantic fantasy film about two teenagers who swap bodies and attempt to find each other across time and space.\n5. **Princess Mononoke** - A story about the struggle between the spirits of the forest and humans seeking to exploit its resources.\n\nThese examples represent only a fraction of the vast world of hand-drawn anime. Each series and film brings its own unique artistry and storytelling, contributing to the rich tapestry of anime history and culture.",
